
Integrated Development Environment (IDE):
IntelliJ IDEA (Community or Ultimate Edition): Excellent for Java development with robust features.

Build Tools:
Maven: For managing dependencies and project builds.

Web Frameworks:
Spring Boot: Simplifies creating web applications and microservices.

Web Servers:
Apache Tomcat: A lightweight servlet container for deploying Java web apps.

Frontend Tools :
Thymeleaf: A Java template engine for creating dynamic HTML pages.

Database Management:
MySQL: Relational databases for managing application data.
Hibernate: An Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) framework for simplifying database interactions.
Version Control & Collaboration:
Git: Essential for version control. Use platforms like GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket.
